8 0 obj
<< /Length 1848 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (HOW CHILDREN GRIEVE \(By Age\)) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 686.0 Td (Under 3 years:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 670.0 Td (- Don't understand death but sense absence and parent's grief) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 656.0 Td (- May regress \(sleep, feeding, clinging\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.0 Td (- Need: routine, physical comfort, simple honest words) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 624.0 Td (Ages 3-5:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 608.0 Td (- Think death is temporary/reversible \(like sleep\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 594.0 Td (- Magical thinking \('Did I cause this?'\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 580.0 Td (- May ask the same questions repeatedly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 566.0 Td (- Need: concrete explanations, reassurance, play-based processing) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 548.0 Td (Ages 6-9:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 532.0 Td (- Understand death is permanent but may not grasp it happening to them) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 518.0 Td (- May worry about other people dying) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 504.0 Td (- Can seem fine then suddenly collapse in grief) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 490.0 Td (- Need: factual info, permission to feel, continued normalcy) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 472.0 Td (Ages 10-12:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 456.0 Td (- Understand death fully) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 442.0 Td (- May hide emotions to 'protect' parents) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 428.0 Td (- Risk of anger, acting out, withdrawal) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 414.0 Td (- Need: honest conversations, peer support, counseling access) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 396.0 Td (Teens:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 380.0 Td (- Grieve like adults but with fewer coping tools) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 366.0 Td (- May turn to peers instead of parents) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 352.0 Td (- Risk of substance use, reckless behavior) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 338.0 Td (- Need: space AND availability, professional support offered) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
